cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.GR, cs.MM, cs.LG. 

The paper proposes a method for registering multiple views of a scene to generate a complete geometric and appearance model of it, which is a common problem in computer vision and robotics. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also mentions applications such as robot guidance and scene mapping, which suggest that it could also belong to cs.RO (Robotics). The method involves using 3D point sets and depth-sensing cameras, which could fall under cs.GR (Graphics) or cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper evaluates the proposed method using quantitative metrics, which could indicate that it belongs to cs.LG (Machine Learning).
